FBIS4-38467 "drsov104_h_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-104 Daily Report 28 May 1994 Moldova Further on Assassination Attempt Further on Assassination Attempt AU3005170594 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1904 GMT 28 May 94 AU3005170594 Chisinau BASAPRESS English BFN [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 28/5/1994 -- Immediately after the explosion of a bomb in Boris Luchik's apartment he and one of his bodyguards were hospitalized at the Centre of Burns from Odessa. In the attempt Luchik received burns covering 60 percent of his body, his bodyguard 75 percent. Boris Luchik's wife, Valentina died just after the explosion. Tiraspol officials gave the opinion on the local radio that the attempt on prosecutor's life was advantageous for Colonel Bergman, commander of the military division, who was earlier under investigation. The commander of the 14th Army declared that the attempt was probably organized by Vadim Shevtsov (Antyufeyev), as the Dniester prosecutor had authorized the arrest of Limanskiy, ex-deputy chairman of the Slobozia District Soviet.
